crop_field.description: A field can be used to cultivate wheat, potato, corn, or cotton. Crops can be used for human feed, animal feed, textile manufacturing, or processing into other products.

fruit_field.description: A field can be used to cultivate apples, oranges, or pears. Fruits can be used for human and animal feed.

pasture.description: A pasture can be used to graze cows, pigs, sheep, or chicken. Animals turn into meat and leather products, which can be used for human feed and textiles. Pastures need a supply of crops to operate.

cattle_shed.description: A cattle shed can be used for raising cattle. Animals turn into meat and leather products, which can be used for human feed and textiles. Cattle sheds need a supply of crops to operate.

flour_mill.description: A flour mill grinds crops into flour. Flour can be processed into pastries. Flour mills need a supply of crops to operate.

milking_parlor.description: A milking parlor milks cows into dairy products, which can be used for human feed. Milking parlors need a supply of crops to operate.

slaughterhouse.description: A slaughterhouse slaughters animals into meat, which can be used for human feed. Slaughterhouses need a supply of crops to operate.

fishing_grounds.description: Fishing grounds allow people to catch fish. Fish can be used for human feed.

fish_farm.description: A fish farm gathers fish in high yields. Fish can be used for human feed.

algae_farm.description: An algae farm gathers algae in high yields. Fish can be used for human feed.

seaweed_farm.description: A seaweed farm gathers seaweed in high yields. Fish can be used for human feed.

tree_plantation.description: A tree plantation can be used to cultivate alder, beech, or conifer. Wood can be used for construction, or processed into timber.

sapling_field.description: A field can be used to plant tree saplings. Wood can be used for construction, or processed into timber.

sawmill.description: A sawmill planes wood into lumber. Planed timber can be used for construction. Sawmills need a supply of wood to operate.

biomass_pellet_plant.description: A biomass pellet plant processes wood into biomass pellets. Paper can be used for printing. Biomass pellet plants need a supply of wood to operate.

engineered_wood_plant.description: An engineered wood plant engineers wood into lumber. Timber can be used for construction. Engineered wood plants need a supply of wood to operate.

pulp_mill.description: A pulp mill pulps wood into paper, which can be used for printing. Pulp mills need a supply of wood to operate.

quarry.description: A quarry excavates stone from the earth for construction.

ore_mine.description: An ore mine excavates ore from Earth's ore deposits.

ore_grinding_mill.description: An ore grinding mill grinds ore into usable metals. Ore grinding mills need a supply of ore to operate.

glass_manufacturing_plant.description: A glass manufacturing plant manufactures ores into sheets of glass. Glass manufacturing plants need a supply of ore to operate.

rotary_kiln_plant.description: A rotary kiln plant heats ore to form metals. Rotary kiln plants need a supply of ore to operate.

fiberglass_plant.description: A fiberglass plant produces glass. Fiberglass plants need a supply of ore to operate.

oil_rig.description: An oil rig extracts oil from the earth.

oil_sludge_prolysis_plant.description: An oil sludge pyrolysis plant refines oil into petroleum. Oil sludge pyrolysis plants need a supply of oil to operate.

petrochemical_plant.description: A petrochemical plant produces polymers and oilgomers. Plastic can be processed into toys. Petrochemical plants need a supply of oil to operate.

waste_oil_refining_plant.description: A waste oil refining plant produces petroleum. Waste oil refining plants need a supply of oil to operate.

naphtha_cracker_plant.description: A naphtha cracker plant produces plastics. Plastic can be processed into toys and household plastic. Naphtha cracker plants need a supply of oil to operate.

seafood_factory.description: A seafood factory processes fish into seafood products for human feed. Seafood factories need supplies of fish and plastic to operate.

furniture_factory.description: A furniture factory manufactures furniture for profit. Furniture factories need supplies of timber and paper to operate.

bakery.description: A bakery produces pastries for human feed. Bakeries need supply of meat, crops, and flour to operate.

steel_plant.description: A steel plant processes iron into steel. Steel plants need a supply of iron to operate.

household_plastic_factory.description: A household plastic factory produces household plastic products for profit. Household plastic factories need supplies of petroleum and plastic to operate.

toy_factory.description: A toy factory produces toys to entertain the children whilst making a profit. Toy factories need supplies of paper, timber, and plastic to operate.

printing_press.description: A printing press prints paper into reading material for profit. Printing presses need supplies of paper and plastic to operate.

lemonade_factory.description: A lemonade factory produces refreshing lemonade for human consumption. Lemonade factories need supplies of crops and plastic to operate.

electronics_factory.description: An electronics factory produces electronics for profit. Electronics factories need supplies of plastic, glass, and copper to operate.

textile_mill.description: A textile mill produces textile clothing for profit. Textiler mills need supplies of meat, crops, and plastic to operate.

petroleum_refinery.description: A petroleum refinery refines petroleum into fuel. Petroleum refineries need supplies of petroleum, plastic, and iron to operate.

soft_paper_factory.description: A soft paper factory softens paper into tissues and toilet paper. Soft paper factories need supplies of crops, paper, petroleum, and plastic to operate.

car_factory.description: A car factory manufactures cars and other automobiles for profit. Car factories need supplies of meat, plastic, glass, and iron to operate.

food_processing_facility.description: A food factory manufactures convenience food for human feed. Food factories need supplies of crops, meat, flour, paper, and plastic to operate.

sneaker_factory.description: A sneaker factory manufactures shoes for profit. Sneaker factories need supplies of crops, meat, paper, petroleum, and plastic to operate.

modular_house_factory.description: A modular house factory manufactures houses for human residence. Modular house factories need supplies of timber, plastic, glass, copper, stone, and iron to operate.

shipyard.description: A shipyard assembles cruise ships for sea travel. Shipyards need supplies of timber, plastic, glass, and iron to operate.

aluminum_factory.description: An aluminium factory processes bauxite into aluminium. Aluminium factories need a supply of bauxite to operate.

ammunition_factory.description: An ammunition factory manufactures ammunition for profit (if personal firearm possession is legal in your country) and for warfare. Ammunition factories need supplies of copper and iron to operate.

artillery_factory.description: An artillery factory manufactures artillery for warfare. Artillery factories need a supply of steel to operate.

concrete_factory.description: A concrete factory manufactures concrete for infrastructure. Concrete factories need a supply of stone to operate.

firearms_factory.description: A firearms factory manufactures firearms for profit (if personal firearm possession is legal in your country) and for warfare. Firearms factories need supplies of timber and steel to operate.

market.description: The town market is the hub of economic activity for a small economy.

main_street.description: The Main Street is the economic center of a small town, where business ventures congregate.
